{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Normal}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Zigzagoon}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Normal|prevnum=262|prev=Mightyena|nextnum=264|next=Linoone|roundleft=bl|roundright=br}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Zigzagoon\n|jname=ジグザグマ\n|tmname=Jiguzaguma\n|forme=2\n|form1=Zigzagoon\n|form2=Galarian Zigzagoon\n|image2=263Zigzagoon-Galar.png\n|ndex=263\n|type1=Normal\n|form2type1=Dark\n|form2type2=Normal\n|category={{tt|Tiny Raccoon|TinyRaccoon before Generation VI}}\n|height-ftin=1\'04"\n|height-m=0.4\n|weight-lbs=38.6\n|weight-kg=17.5\n|abilitylayout=2\n|ability1=Pickup\n|ability2=Gluttony\n|abilityd=Quick Feet\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Field\n|eggcycles=15\n|evtotal=1\n|evsp=1\n|expyield=56<!--48 in Gen V-VI-->\n|oldexp=60\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Brown\n|catchrate=255\n|body=08\n|pokefordex=zigzagoon\n|generation=3\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Zigzagoon\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ジグザグマ\'\'\' \'\'Jiguzaguma\'\') is a {{type|Normal}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation III]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolve]]s into {{p|Linoone}} starting at [[level]] 20.\n\nIn [[Galar]], Zigzagoon has a [[regional variant]] that is {{2t|Dark|Normal}}. It evolves into Galarian Linoone starting at level 20, which evolves into {{p|Obstagoon}} when leveled up at [[Time|night]] starting at level 35.\n\n==Biology==\nZigzagoon is a raccoon-like, quadruped Pokémon with bristly, zigzag-patterned fur. It has stripes formed by alternating layers of cream and brown fur. It has a brown head with spiky ears and a black nose. A black, mask pattern surrounds its brown eyes. The upper half of its mouth is jagged, and when it is open, there are two pointed teeth in its lower jaw. Its feet have three claws and pink paw pads. Its forefeet are cream-colored, but the hind feet are brown. Its brush tail is spiky and bristly.\n\nZigzagoon is abundantly curious, as it wanders restlessly back and forth while rubbing its nose to the ground in search of something. It rubs its bristly back hair against trees to mark its territory, and plays dead to fool opponents in battle. Zigzagoon is found commonly in {{DL|List of Pokémon by habitat|Grassland Pokémon|grassy fields}}.\n\n==In the anime==\n===In the main series===\n[[File:Professor Sycamore Zigzagoon.png|thumb|left|200px|Zigzagoon in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n====Major appearances====\nMultiple Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[AG005|In the Knicker of Time]]\'\', where [[Nicholai]] spent much of the episode trying to {{pkmn2|caught|catch}} one. He was eventually successful. Nicholai\'s Zigzagoon reappeared in \'\'[[AG048|Zig Zag Zangoose!]]\'\'. In both episodes, it was used in a battle against {{Ash}} and his Pokémon.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[HS05|The Blue Badge of Courage]]\'\', under the ownership of one of the [[Gym Badge thieves]]. It and a {{p|Poochyena}} battled [[Misty\'s Psyduck]] and [[Sakura\'s Espeon]], but both were defeated.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[AG046|Candid Camerupt!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Winstrate family|Victor Winstrate]]. It battled [[Brock\'s Mudkip]] and was able to defeat it using {{m|Thunderbolt}}.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[XY088|A Trip Down Memory Train!]]\'\', where it was among the group of Pokémon that befriended [[Clemont\'s Bunnelby]] when it was still a wild Pokémon.\n\n====Minor appearances====\nZigzagoon debuted in \'\'[[EP272|Johto Photo Finish]]\'\', where it was seen in {{jo|Harrison}}\'s explanation of the Hoenn region.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[AG008|A Tail with a Twist]]\'\'.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[AG010|You Said a Mouthful!]]\'\'\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[AG011|A Bite to Remember]]\'\'.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[AG030|A Meditite Fight!]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn|Coordinator}}\'s Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[AG033|Now That\'s Flower Power!]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[M07|Destiny Deoxys]]\'\'.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[AG089|A Scare to Remember!]]\'\'.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[AG106|Beg, Burrow and Steal]]\'\'.\n\nA Coordinator\'s Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[AG115|Mean With Envy]]\'\'.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[AG121|Hi Ho Silver Wind!]]\'\', under the ownership of a Coordinator.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[AG159|Off the Unbeaten Path]]\'\', where it was participating in the [[Pokémon Orienteering]] competition.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[AG172|Pokémon Ranger - Deoxys\' Crisis! (Part 2)]]\'\'.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[DP001|Following A Maiden\'s Voyage!]]\'\'.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[DP028|Drifloon On the Wind!]]\'\'.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[DP034|Buizel Your Way Out Of This!]]\'\', under the ownership of a {{tc|Fisherman}}. It was carried in after being knocked out by a {{AP|Buizel}}.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[DP038|One Big Happiny Family!]]\'\' in [[Jessie]]\'s fantasy.\n\nMultiple Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[M13|Zoroark: Master of Illusions]]\'\' as one of the many Pokémon residing in [[Crown City]]. Two Zigzagoon worked with several other Pokémon in surrounding {{OBP|Zorua|M13}} in the park in order to attack him as retribution for what {{OBP|Zoroark|M13}} did to the city. Before a fight broke out, the Zigzagoon, along with the other Pokémon, were calmed down by {{OBP|Celebi|M13}}.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[XY001|Kalos, Where Dreams and Adventures Begin!]]\'\'.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[XY002|Lumiose City Pursuit!]]\'\', \'\'[[XY010|Mega-Mega Meowth Madness!]]\'\', \'\'[[XY040|Day Three Blockbusters!]]\'\', and \'\'[[XY137|Battling With a Clean Slate!]]\'\'; and in a flashback in \'\'[[XYS01|Mega Evolution Special I]]\'\' and \'\'[[XY068|Garchomp\'s Mega Bond!]]\'\' at {{an|Professor Sycamore}}\'s lab.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[XY003|A Battle of Aerial Mobility!]]\'\'.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[XY018|Awakening the Sleeping Giant]]\'\'.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in a flashback or a fantasy in \'\'[[XY035|The Forest Champion!]]\'\'.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[M17|Diancie and the Cocoon of Destruction]]\'\' as a resident of [[Allearth Forest]].\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[PK27|Pikachu and the Pokémon Music Squad]]\'\'. It was among the Pokémon residing in a forest.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[XYS04|Mega Evolution Special IV]]\'\'.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[XY096|A Giga Battle with Mega Results!]]\'\'.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[XY108|A Watershed Moment!]]\'\' in a flashback.\n\nA Trainer\'s Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[XY111|Unlocking Some Respect!]]\'\'.\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[XY121|Seeing the Forest for the Trees!]]\'\', where it, along with a {{p|Scatterbug}}, {{p|Oddish}}, {{p|Budew}}, and {{p|Sentret}}, were brought into a cave to join Ash in the [[Winding Woods]].\n\nTwo Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[M19|Volcanion and the Mechanical Marvel]]\'\' as residents of the [[Nebel Plateau]].\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Animedexheader|Hoenn}}\n{{Animedexbody|AG005|Zigzagoon|Ash\'s Pokédex|Zigzagoon, the TinyRaccoon Pokémon. Zigzagoon is extremely curious and so ends up walking in a zigzag path between things that interest it.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Advanced Generation\'\'|Hoenn}}\n\n===In the Pokémon Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire Animated Trailer===\n[[File:Youngster Zigzagoon ORAS Trailer.png|thumb|250px|Zigzagoon in the animated trailer]]\nA Zigzagoon appeared in the [[Pokémon Omega Ruby and Pokémon Alpha Sapphire Animated Trailer]], under the ownership of a {{tc|Youngster}}. It battled against {{ga|Brendan}}\'s {{p|Treecko}}.\n{{-}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Kylee Zigzagoon Adventures.png|thumb|150px|Zigzagoon in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the movie adaptations===\nA Zigzagoon appeared in the {{ma|Diancie and the Cocoon of Destruction|manga adaptation}} of \'\'[[M17|Diancie and the Cocoon of Destruction]]\'\' as a resident of [[Allearth Forest]].\n\nA Zigzagoon appeared in the {{ma|Volcanion and the Mechanical Marvel|manga adaptation}} of \'\'[[M19|Volcanion and the Mechanical Marvel]]\'\' as a resident of the [[Nebel Plateau]].\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nA Zigzagoon made a cameo appearance at the end of \'\'[[PS180|The Last Battle XIV]]\'\', where one was being examined by [[Professor Elm]].\n\nA {{pkmn2|wild}} Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[PS182|Making Mirth with Mightyena]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[PS204|Plugging Past Electrike I]]\'\'.\n\n{{adv|Sapphire}} encountered {{tc|Picnicker|a young Trainer}} and her sick Zigzagoon in \'\'[[PS226|I Dare Ya, Altaria... Knock Chic off My Shoulder]]\'\'. Her way of healing the Zigzagoon caught [[Winona]]\'s attention.\n\nA Trainer\'s Zigzagoon appeared in \'\'[[PS253|A Royal Rumble with Regirock, Regice and Registeel I]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Ruby-Sapphire manga===\nIn the [[Pokémon Ruby-Sapphire]] manga, a Zigzagoon appears in the chapter \'\'[[PMRS01|Let\'s Go Catch The Dumpling Thief!!]]\'\'. [[Red\'s Clefairy]] is accused of stealing dumplings from a shrine, but it turns out that they were being eaten by a mischievous Zigzagoon.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Zigzagoon (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===NPC appearances===\n* [[Pokémon Pinball: Ruby & Sapphire]]: Zigzagoon sits to the left of the [[Sapphire Field]] and will change its position when the ball hits the button in front of it. When Zigzagoon is positioned to pounce, it will immediately stop the slot machine when the A button is pressed, allowing for the prize to be chosen by the player.\n* {{game|Emerald}}: At the beginning of the game, a wild Zigzagoon attacks Professor Birch. The player must use his/her [[starter Pokémon]] to defeat it.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n<!--====Zigzagoon====-->\n{{Dex/Header|type=Normal}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=III}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=III|reg1=Hoenn|num1=012|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Ruby|t=FFF|entry=Zigzagoon restles